Q1> A computer is an elctronic device which is used to store, process and compute information and give us a required result.
Q2> RAM stands for random access memory. It is one of the components of a computer which is used to store information temporarily. It is fast and compact as it is made up of magnetic material.
Q3> Inside a computer data is stored in the Hard Disk Drive as it is non volatile in nature which means that the information is stored permanently even after we turn off the computer.
